# 11. Practical Recommendations

The authors provide several practical recommendations for improving TinyML engineering practices.

Examples include:

- Development of hardware-aware neural architecture search methods.
- Creation of standardized TinyML benchmarking frameworks.
- Development of portable libraries for pre-processing and post-processing tasks.
- Integration of TinyML workflows into development toolchains.
- Support for device emulation to test compiled models before deployment.
- Implementation of OTA updates for firmware and TinyML models.

---

# 12. Limitations of the Review

The paper acknowledges several limitations.

- TinyML is a rapidly evolving field.
- The amount of published research is still limited.
- The study includes grey literature sources.
- No industry surveys or interviews were conducted.
- Future advances may change the conclusions and proposed workflows.

---

# 13. Methodological Strengths of This SLR

The review presents several methodological strengths.

- Clearly defined research questions (RQ1 and RQ2).
- Use of multiple academic databases.
- Explicit search strings.
- Use of forward and backward snowballing.
- Defined inclusion and exclusion criteria.
- Clear reporting of selection counts.
- Structured tables summarizing extracted knowledge.

---

# 14. Potential Methodological Weaknesses

The study also presents several methodological limitations.

- No PRISMA flow diagram.
- No formal quality assessment of studies.
- No defined search time window.
- Screening process only partially described.
- Small dataset (33 sources).
- Inclusion of grey literature may introduce bias.
- No explicit data extraction protocol.

